{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. CONDO COMMUNITY STREET - DUSK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Saab rounds a corner and parks in front of a modest CONDO.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SUPERIMPOSE:
{META_DATA}: OXNARD, CALIFORNIA
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. MILES'S MOTHER'S CONDO - DUSK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Approaching the front door, Miles pulls a BOUQUET OF FLOWERS out of a plastic grocery store bag.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack carries a bottle of CHAMPAGNE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles pulls a BIRTHDAY CARD out of the bag too.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: Wait a second.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pulls a PEN from his pocket and signs it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As he licks the envelope, Jack rings the bell.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Moments later PHYLLIS comes to the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is a matronly older woman in a nightgown and housecoat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES AND JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Surprise!
{DIALOGUE}: Happy Birthday!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The boys offer up the flowers and champagne.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Phyllis slurs slightly as she speaks -- she's been doing some celebrating of her own.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PHYLLIS
{DIALOGUE}: My God.
{DIALOGUE}: Miles.
{DIALOGUE}: And Jack!
{DIALOGUE}: What a surprise.
{DIALOGUE}: I can't remember the last time you brought me flowers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They hug.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: They're from both of us.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PHYLLIS
{DIALOGUE}: A famous actor bringing me flowers on my birthday.
{DIALOGUE}: Don't I feel special?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: A famous actor who's getting married next week.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PHYLLIS
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, that's right.
{DIALOGUE}: Isn't that nice?
{DIALOGUE}: I hope that girls knows how lucky she is, marrying no less than Derek Summersby.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The boys follow her inside.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MILES'S MOTHER'S CONDO - CONTINUOUS
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Jeez, Mrs. Raymond, that was eleven years ago.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PHYLLIS
{DIALOGUE}: Well, you were wonderful on that show.
{DIALOGUE}: I never understood why they had to give you that brain tumor so soon.
{DIALOGUE}: Why that didn't make you the biggest movie star in the world is a sin.
{DIALOGUE}: It's a sin.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, well, you should be my agent.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PHYLLIS
{DIALOGUE}: If I was, I would sing your praises up and down the street until they put me in the loony bin.
{DIALOGUE}: Now Miles, why didn't you tell me you were coming and bringing this handsome man?
{DIALOGUE}: Look how I'm dressed.
{DIALOGUE}: I've got to run and put my face on.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: You look fabulous, Mrs. Raymond.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PHYLLIS
{META_DATA}: (over her shoulder)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, stop it.
{DIALOGUE}: Make yourselves comfortable.
{META_DATA}: (now around the corner)
{DIALOGUE}: You boys hungry?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, I'm hungry.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack gives Miles a look.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{META_DATA}: (low)
{DIALOGUE}: Just a snack.
{DIALOGUE}: Calm down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles leads Jack into this small condo.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The TV is on, and it's MESSY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Amid the newspapers and junk mail and dishes, an AB-ROLLER and an ancient SCHWINN EXER-CYCLE sit forgotten in a corner.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MILES'S MOTHER'S KITCHEN - NIGHT
