{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MUSIC STARTS -- they're OFF!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DINNER is improvised, but includes:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: -- The arrival of the FIRST WINE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: -- The SALADS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: -- Maya takes a turn with the wine list.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles pushes her finger down into the prices with THREE DIGITS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: -- New stemware is provided with the arrival of the SECOND WINE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: -- The four of them DRINK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Particularly Miles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: -- Stephanie and Jack get cozier and cozier.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: -- The SALMON and DUCK arrive.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: -- Miles is too shy to look into Maya's eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She's interested and available -- it's too much for him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: -- As Miles gets DRUNKER, the camera angles become sloppier, the cutting choppier.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: -- Miles PONTIFICATES about some aspect of wine that Maya and Stephanie find interesting.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Left out in the cold, his jaw tight, Jack wants to find a way in but can't.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: -- Miles reaches over to refill his glass, but Jack's arm shoots out to stop him -- "Slow down."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON MILES as a distant RUMBLE begins to sound, the rumble of an oncoming ANXIETY ATTACK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: By now he has drunk so much that he spaces out, descending into --
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. UNDERWORLD - DARK AND TIMELESS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles is boarding an OPEN BOAT atop this underground river, the River Styx.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Just beyond a ghoulish HUMAN CARGO the hooded boatman CHARON wields a long staff.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles is crossing over to the dark side.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. LOS OLIVOS CAFE - BACK AGAIN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles returns to earth to find Jack and Stephanie now in their own little world -- Jack explaining something to Stephanie that she finds fascinating, just FASCINATING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: -- Miles converses with Maya, but it's clear from her bemused expression that he's being charming if not entirely coherent.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: -- ANOTHER WINE reaches the table -- a Comte Armand Pornrnard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: -- Miles looks over at Jack and Stephanie.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They share a short but sensual kiss.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOMENTS LATER --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles is on his feet threading his way through the tables.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is very unsteady, and we cut between first and third person perspectives.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AT THE BATHROOMS --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He tries the MEN'S ROOM door but it's locked.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pulls the XANAX out his pocket and pops one in his mouth, swallowing it dry.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He notices a PAYPHONE nearby.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Thinking better of it for a moment, Miles makes a drunken bee-line for the receiver.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON THE KEYPAD --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as many numbers are dialed, and we HEAR the TONES, completely out of sync, along with a sound melange of interior phone RINGING and a PICKUP.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE RECEIVER --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Miles presses it desperately to his head.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VICTORIA (ON THE PHONE)
{DIALOGUE}: Hello?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: Victoria.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VICTORIA (ON THE PHONE)
{DIALOGUE}: Miles?
