{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: My palate's kind of shot, but from what I can tell, I'd dub it pretty damn good.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAYA
{DIALOGUE}: Can I ask you a personal question?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{META_DATA}: (bracing himself)
{DIALOGUE}: Sure.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAYA
{DIALOGUE}: Why are you so into Pinot?
{DIALOGUE}: It's like a thing with you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles laughs at first, then smiles wistfully at the question.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He searches for the answer in his glass and begins slowly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know.
{DIALOGUE}: It's a hard grape to grow.
{DIALOGUE}: As you know.
{DIALOGUE}: It's thin-skinned, temperamental, ripens early.
{DIALOGUE}: It's not a survivor like Cabernet that can grow anywhere and thrive even when neglected.
{DIALOGUE}: Pinot needs constant care and attention and in fact can only grow in specific little tucked- away corners of the world.
{DIALOGUE}: And only the most patient and nurturing growers can do it really, can tap into Pinot's most fragile, delicate qualities.
{DIALOGUE}: Only when someone has taken the time to truly understand its potential can Pinot be coaxed into its fullest expression.
{DIALOGUE}: And when that happens, its flavors are the most haunting and brilliant and subtle and thrilling and ancient on the planet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Maya has found this answer revealing and moving.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: I mean, Cabernets can be powerful and exalting, but they seem prosaic to me for some reason.
{DIALOGUE}: By comparison.
{DIALOGUE}: How about you?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAYA
{DIALOGUE}: What about me?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know.
{DIALOGUE}: Why are you into wine?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAYA
{DIALOGUE}: I suppose I got really into wine originally through my ex-husband.
{DIALOGUE}: He had a big, kind of show-off cellar.
{DIALOGUE}: But then I found out that I have a really sharp palate, and the more I drank, the more I liked what it made me think about.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah?
{DIALOGUE}: Like what?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAYA
{DIALOGUE}: Like what a fraud he was.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles laughs.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAYA
{DIALOGUE}: No, but I do like to think about the life of wine, how it's a living thing.
{DIALOGUE}: I like to think about what was going on the year the grapes were growing, how the sun was shining that summer or if it rained... what the weather was like.
{DIALOGUE}: I think about all those people who tended and picked the grapes, and if it's an old wine, how many of them must be dead by now.
{DIALOGUE}: I love how wine continues to evolve, how every time I open a bottle it's going to taste different than if I had opened it on any other day.
{DIALOGUE}: Because a bottle of wine is actually alive -- it's constantly evolving and gaining complexity.
{DIALOGUE}: That is, until it peaks -- like your '61 -- and begins its steady, inevitable decline.
{DIALOGUE}: And it tastes so fucking good.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Now it is Miles's turn to be swept away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Maya's face tells us the moment is right, but Miles remains frozen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He needs another sign, and Maya is bold enough to offer it: reaches out and places one hand atop his.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{META_DATA}: (pointing)
{DIALOGUE}: Bathroom over there?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAYA
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles gets up and walks out.
