{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then he hears a noise from the kitchen, so he goes through the door into --
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. STEPHANIE'S KITCHEN - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Maya is at the sink, filling a glass with water.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAYA
{DIALOGUE}: I was just getting some water.
{DIALOGUE}: You want some water?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles goes to stand by her and accepts a glass of water.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Just as she's about to fill a second glass, he stops her and looks her in the eye, trying to recapture a moment that is long gone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He kisses her and she kisses back, but the whole thing feels strained and awkward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: After a few seconds, Maya breaks away.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAYA
{DIALOGUE}: Nice.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But instead of resuming the kiss, she steps past him, heading back into the living room.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAYA (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: I should probably get going.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles realizes he's blown it and silently berates himself.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SAAB - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles drives down the hill behind Maya's car, which leads him through this very rural road.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. WHERE THE ROAD MEETS THE HIGHWAY - NIGHT
