{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OMIT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: UNDER BLACK --
{META_DATA}: TUESDAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack's cellphone RINGS.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MOTEL ROOM - MORNING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: NOW EARLY MORNING --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Still fully clothed, Miles staggers across the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fishing the phone out of Jack's windbreaker pocket, he looks at the CALLER ID: "Erganian, Christine" and the number.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He briefly considers his options -- answer it?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: shut it off?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: -- before placing it atop Jack's suitcase.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The moment he lies back down on the bed, the MOTEL PHONE RINGS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An old DIGITAL CLOCK next to it reads 7:l0.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Miles closes his eyes and pulls the pillow over his aching head, we again --
{META_DATA}: FADE TO BLACK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LATER --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: VROOM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Outside a roaring MOTORCYCLE comes to a stop.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then over the sound of an IDLING ENGINE come familiar if indistinct VOICES and LAUGHTER.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles opens his bleary eyes and listens.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FOOTSTEPS pound on the balcony outside, and Jack lets himself in, flushed and exuberant.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Fucking chick is unbelievable.
{DIALOGUE}: Un-be- lieve-able!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pounds on the wall, then goes into the bathroom and without closing the door unzips his pants to PEE.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Goddamn, Miles, she is nasty.
{DIALOGUE}: Nasty nasty nasty.
