{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. DRIVING RANGE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles DRIVES ball after ball, unsuccessfully trying to release his frustration.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BUCOLIC ROAD - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Saab roars past us, perhaps going a little too fast.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SAAB - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Whistling absently as he drives, Miles leans over to turn the radio on and fiddle around to find a good station.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then all of a sudden --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WHUMP!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The car has struck something with a hideous sound followed immediately by the receding "ARF-ARF-ARF-ARF" of an injured DOG in the Saab's wake.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles applies the BRAKES.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BUCOLIC ROAD - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles gets out of his car just in time to see --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A DOG
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: scampering into the nearby woods.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles looks around -- has anyone seen him?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Is there a nearby residence?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Finding nothing, Miles momentarily weighs his options before finally GIVING CHASE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He follows the path of the dog into --
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. ROADSIDE WOODS - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Still hearing occasional distant barking, Miles finds his way among the trees and bushes, looking in vain for the ill- fated cur.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: After a frenetic search, Miles reluctantly gives up and heads back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OMIT.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BUCOLIC ROAD - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles has returned to where he hit the dog.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Just then, Miles notices TWO MEXICAN CHILDREN watching him from just down the road.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They disappear into the bushes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Looking like a criminal, Miles trots back to the Saab climbs behind the wheel and speeds away.
