{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Startled, Miles turns to look at --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A PRIEST
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: who is singing the BLESSING OF THE RINGS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We are now in --
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ARMENIAN APOSTOLIC CHURCH - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The church is packed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON THE RINGS as the priest holds them aloft.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: If those rings could talk... Jack shoots a quick look at Miles, who looks right back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The priest continues his blessing.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. ARMENIAN CHURCH - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AT THE TOP OF THE STAIRS --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The WEDDING FAMILIES greet the exiting guests in a RECEIVING LINE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Smiling and exuberant, Jack seems utterly at home as the new groom.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AT THE BOTTOM OF THE STEPS --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles watches the scene, not without melancholy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VICTORIA (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Hey, Miles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles turns and looks up to see Victoria, standing one step above him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Just behind her is her NEW HUSBAND.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He exudes the quiet confidence of a successful businessman who played college football, takes expensive skiing and sailing vacations, and hasn't read a novel since high school.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: Hi, Vicki.
{META_DATA}: (taking her in)
{DIALOGUE}: You look beautiful.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VICTORIA
{DIALOGUE}: Thanks.
{DIALOGUE}: Um, this is Ken Cortland, my husband.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: From his spot hovering over Miles, Ken leans down and offers his hand.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KEN
{DIALOGUE}: How are you?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: Hi.
{DIALOGUE}: How you doing?
{DIALOGUE}: You're a lucky guy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KEN
{DIALOGUE}: Thanks.
{META_DATA}: (to Victoria)
{DIALOGUE}: I'll wait for you at the car.
{META_DATA}: (to Miles)
{DIALOGUE}: Nice to meet you, Miles.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: Ken.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exit Ken.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: That was big of him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VICTORIA
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, he's good that way.
{DIALOGUE}: Very considerate.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: That's great.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VICTORIA
{DIALOGUE}: So how're you doing?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: Since the last time we spoke?
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know.
{DIALOGUE}: Could be better.
{DIALOGUE}: Could be worse.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VICTORIA
{DIALOGUE}: So what's happening with your book?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: Universally rejected.
{DIALOGUE}: Strike three.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VICTORIA
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, Miles.
{DIALOGUE}: That's awful.
{DIALOGUE}: What are you going to do?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: Back to the drawing board, I guess.
{DIALOGUE}: Or not.
{DIALOGUE}: So... you're married.
{DIALOGUE}: Congratulations.
{DIALOGUE}: You look happy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VICTORIA
{DIALOGUE}: I am.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: Seems like everyone's getting married.
{DIALOGUE}: A year ago it was all divorces.
{DIALOGUE}: Now it's all weddings.
{DIALOGUE}: Cyclical, I guess.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VICTORIA
{DIALOGUE}: I guess.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Just then a BLACK LINCOLN NAVIGATOR pulls up alongside the curb.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The passenger side window is halfway down, and the sounds of Adult Contemporary Jazz waft out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Victoria gives Ken a little wave.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{META_DATA}: (shifting gears)
{DIALOGUE}: Well, let's go have some champagne, shall we?
{DIALOGUE}: Toast all the newlyweds.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VICTORIA
{DIALOGUE}: Not me.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm not drinking.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: You quit drinking?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VICTORIA
{DIALOGUE}: I'm pregnant.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{META_DATA}: (hit in the solar plexus)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh.
{DIALOGUE}: Huh.
{DIALOGUE}: Well...
{META_DATA}: (rallying)
{DIALOGUE}: Congratulations again, Vicki.
{DIALOGUE}: That's wonderful news.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VICTORIA
{META_DATA}: (going to the car)
{DIALOGUE}: See you over there, Miles.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As she gets in the car and cruises away, Miles glances back at --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE RECEIVING LINE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: -- where Mike Erganian is introducing Jack to some dear old FRIENDS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mike throws a loving arm around his new son-in-law, and Jack is drawn into Mike's bosom.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. STREET - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A HAND-PAINTED SIGN, attached to a STOP SIGH and decorated with balloons, reads: "RECEPTION THIS WAY!"
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: with an arrow pointing RIGHT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One by one, CARS are making a right turn.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But when his turn comes, Miles turns LEFT.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. MILES'S APARTMENT COMPLEX - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Saab pull up outside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles leaves the car idling as he sprints inside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Moments later he sprints back to his car, this time carrying SOMETHING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OMIT
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. FAST FOOD PLACE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His bowtie undone, Miles sits at a booth eating.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He washes down a bite by draining the contents of a big wax-coated soft drink cup.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He brings the cup to his lap and refills it from a BOTTLE OF WINE hidden next to him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As he sets the bottle back down, we glimpse the label: 1961 Cheval Blanc.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He takes another sip.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the camera MOVES CLOSER, all the complex emotions inspired by the wine ripple across Miles's face.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: 14-YEAR-OLD BOY (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: "The marrow of his bone," I repeated aimlessly.
{DIALOGUE}: This at least penetrated my mind.
{DIALOGUE}: Phineas had died from the marrow of his bone flowing down his blood stream to his heart.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MIDDLE SCHOOL CLASSROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The voice belongs to one of Miles's PUPILS reading aloud in class.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Other students follow along silently from their own copies of A Separate Peace.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SUPERIMPOSED --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FIVE WEEKS LATER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles sits behind his desk at the front of the class.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: 14-YEAR-OLD BOY
{DIALOGUE}: I did not cry then or ever about Finny.
{DIALOGUE}: I did not cry even when I stood watching him being lowered into his family's straight-laced burial ground outside of Boston.
{DIALOGUE}: I could not escape a feeling that this was my own funeral, and you do not cry in that case.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The students look up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: 14-YEAR-OLD BOY
{DIALOGUE}: Do you want me to keep reading the next chapter, Mr. Raymond?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{META_DATA}: (as though coming to)
{DIALOGUE}: Hrnrnrn?
{DIALOGUE}: No, we'll pick up there on Monday.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MILES'S APARTMENT - EVENING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles enters his tiny apartment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He loosens his tie and puts down his satchel.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On his way to the kitchen, he presses a button on his ANSWERING MACHINE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As it plays, he opens the REFRIGERATOR and looks inside.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANSWERING MACHINE
{DIALOGUE}: One new message.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAYA'S VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Hello, Miles.
{DIALOGUE}: It's Maya.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles FREEZES, not wanting to miss a single syllable.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAYA'S VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Thanks for your letter.
{DIALOGUE}: I would have called you sooner, but I think I've needed some time to think about everything that happened and what you wrote to me.
{DIALOGUE}: Another reason I didn't call sooner is that I wanted to finish your book, which I finally did last night.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles's heart pounds.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAYA'S VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: I think it's really lovely, Miles.
{DIALOGUE}: You're so good with words.
{DIALOGUE}: Who cares if it's not getting published?
{DIALOGUE}: There are so many beautiful and painful things about it.
{DIALOGUE}: Did you really go through all that?
{DIALOGUE}: It must have been awfully hard.
{DIALOGUE}: And the sister character -- Jesus, what a wreck.
{DIALOGUE}: But I have to say I was really confused by the ending.
{DIALOGUE}: Did the father finally commit suicide, or what?
{DIALOGUE}: It's driving me crazy.
{DIALOGUE}: And the title.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT./EXT. SAAB - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THROUGH THE WINDSHIELD --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see ourselves taking the BUELLTON EXIT.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAYA'S VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Anyway, it's turned cold and rainy here lately.
{DIALOGUE}: But I like winter.
{DIALOGUE}: So listen, if you ever do decide to come up here again, you should let me know.
{DIALOGUE}: I would say stop by the Hitching Post, but to tell you the truth I'm not sure how much longer I'm going to be working there.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm going to graduate soon so I'll probably relocate.
{DIALOGUE}: We'll see.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. MAYA'S APARTMENT BUILDING - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles climbs the wooden steps and approaches Maya's back door.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAYA'S VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Anyway, like I said, I really loved your novel.
{DIALOGUE}: Don't give up, Miles.
{DIALOGUE}: Keep writing.
{DIALOGUE}: You're really good.
{DIALOGUE}: Hope you're well.
{DIALOGUE}: Bye.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles takes a breath.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Finally he KNOCKS.
{META_DATA}: FADE OUT.
{META_DATA}: THE END
